The paper deals with the analysis of the long run behavior of probabilistic systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science. The study of pattern frequency vectors and their convergence is related to the analysis of formal languages and automata, which is covered by cs.FL. The use of probabilistic models and the approximation of probabilities is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and probability (cs.PR). The study of vector addition systems and their behavior is related to the field of discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science, which is covered by cs.DS and cs.LO. Finally, the discovery of counterexamples in classical results is related to the field of programming languages and compilers, which is covered by cs.PL.
